    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl1302002">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="6">
            <title>REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When you install the bottom reverse idler gear assembly, make sure the three (3) magnetic
                        discs are securely in place at the bottom of the case. Use Eaton Adhesive #71210 or Loctite 277.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The upper reverse idler is positioned in the case during mainshaft installation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If reverse gear assembly is disassembled, position the needle bearing and inner race
                    into the reverse idler gear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13020k7">Figure 207</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13020k7" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13020k7" filename="../figg13/G13020K7.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 207. Reverse Idler Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the rear thrust washer on the idler shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13020k8">Figure 208</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13020k8" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13020k8" filename="../figg13/G13020K8.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 208. Idler Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the idler shaft into the case bore, threaded-end to the front. As the shaft
                    passes through the case bore, position the reverse idler gear on the shaft, long hub to the front (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13020k9">Figure 209</hotlnk>). Insert the thrust washer between the reverse idler
                    gear and the case support boss. Finish inserting the idler shaft.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13020k9" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13020k9" filename="../figg13/G13020K9.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 209. Reverse Idler Gear - Hub To The Front</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the reverse idler shaft is seated in the support boss bore.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the washer and lock nut on shaft front. Tighten the stop nut to 50 to 60 ft-lbs.
                    (68 to 81 N&#8226;m) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13020k9">Figure 209</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13020l0">Figure 210</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13020l0" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13020l0" filename="../figg13/G13020L0.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 210. Washer &#38; Lock Nut</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thread the pipe plug into the reverse idler shaft and tighten (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13020l1">Figure 211</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13020l1" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13020l1" filename="../figg13/G13020L1.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 211. Reverse Idler Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a bearing driver and maul and install the auxiliary countershaft front bearing outer
                    race against the idler plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13020l2">Figure 212</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13020l2" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13020l2" filename="../figg13/G13020L2.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 212. Auxiliary Countershaft</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Make sure the stop nut is properly tightened.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Make sure the bearing outer race is installed against the idler plate.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
